newsitem.title: TUNISIA: Tunisia paid $356.50 c&f for white sugar - traders.
newsitem.headline: Tunisia paid $356.50 c&f for white sugar - traders.

text.p: Tunisia bought a cargo of white sugar for shipment in June 1997 at a snap tender on Monday, traders in Tunis confirmed on Wednesday.
They said the price paid was $356.50 per tonne c & f. Earlier, traders in London said the price was $354.50.

Tunisia bought two 14,000-tonne cargoes of whites on September 18 for May and July, at an undisclosed price. It bought a same-sized cargo the day before from a London-based trade house at $366 per tonne c & f.
